   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Voices Beyond the Walls</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To reduce the rate of re-offending amongst juvenile offenders in Eshowe Correctional Centre, a programme is offered that allows 30 participants in 3 groups of 10 to create radio drama&apos;s that give insights into what is happening on the rural lanscape that brings youth to prison. Drama gives these youths a voice, builds self-confidence and upholds dignity. Radio plays are broadcast by 3 community radio stations locally and 3 performances will be held in the prison.</narrative>
  </description>
